1
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:01,320
Brother Chen.

2
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:03,399
Could this be

3
00:01:03,799 --> 00:01:05,799
Xuanlei Heijing Shan?

4
00:01:10,239 --> 00:01:11,599
It's not black at all.

5
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:17,079
A door.

6
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:21,319
Advisor He.

7
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:24,959
That poem from Dawang's book,

8
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,400
is it reliable?

9
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:29,079
Our ancestors worshipped heavenly gods,

10
00:01:29,719 --> 00:01:31,319
the Mengnagu worshipped the abyss.

11
00:01:31,599 --> 00:01:32,879
So flipping black and white

12
00:01:32,879 --> 00:01:33,840
wouldn't be strange at all.

13
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:35,760
That actually makes sense.

14
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:38,200
The door's open, what are we waiting for?

15
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:39,400
Let's go!

16
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:41,680
Stop!

17
00:01:42,599 --> 00:01:43,280
What is it?

18
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:46,640
What you just said and did

19
00:01:46,799 --> 00:01:48,159
clearly shows that you

20
00:01:48,159 --> 00:01:49,959
seriously lack archaeological experience.

21
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:50,959
What's wrong?

22
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,200
What now?

23
00:02:00,959 --> 00:02:01,719
Let's go.

24
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:03,439
What... what's going on?

25
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,200
There's a trap!

26
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,120
What do we do now?

27
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,840
There's no way to get across!

28
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,680
It even has automatic sensors?

29
00:02:26,159 --> 00:02:27,240
That shouldn't be possible.

30
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:31,360
Ever since we came to Chimei Jizhou,

31
00:02:31,599 --> 00:02:32,840
I've been wondering,

32
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,919
even nowadays,

33
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,360
with all our high-tech tools,

34
00:02:36,599 --> 00:02:38,800
we couldn't even dig a city this deep.

35
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,280
How did the ancient Mengnagu people do it?

36
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,280
That's nothing new, really.

37
00:02:43,439 --> 00:02:44,680
The Egyptians and the Mayans

38
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,280
built pyramids too, didn't they?

39
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,439
That's totally different.

40
00:02:47,479 --> 00:02:48,800
Those are above-ground structures.

41
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,599
They could use pulleys and levers.

42
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,439
But this is underground excavation.

43
00:02:52,919 --> 00:02:55,000
It takes massive manpower and resources,

44
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,280
plus knowledge of geological surveying.

45
00:02:57,639 --> 00:02:59,560
Those passages we just came through

46
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:02,360
had extrusive and plutonic rocks.

47
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,759
So I suspect this used to be a volcano.

48
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,759
A volcano? Again?

49
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,719
Dormant or active?

50
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:10,960
So after all this struggling,

51
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,479
we've been inside a volcano?

52
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,319
That's just our rotten luck.

53
00:03:14,479 --> 00:03:16,039
We just escaped the Dian King,

54
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,680
and now we can't escape the Mengnagu.

55
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,759
What's there to worry about?

56
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:21,000
If this volcano could really erupt,

57
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,599
Chimei Jizhou would be long gone.

58
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,479
I get it now.

59
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,560
This must be a high-temperature rock layer.

60
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,360
High-temperature rock layer?

61
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,840
For rocks to stay this hot,

62
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,800
this place must be an active volcano!

63
00:03:41,599 --> 00:03:43,360
Haven't you heard of hot dry rock?

64
00:03:43,919 --> 00:03:45,280
Hot dry rock?

65
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,080
Right.

66
00:03:47,639 --> 00:03:49,120
It's a high-temperature rock formation.

67
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:51,159
It can reach up to 350 degrees.

68
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,719
Since the 1970s,

69
00:03:52,719 --> 00:03:55,479
other countries have used it for power.

70
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,360
That makes sense.

71
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:58,800
So beneath this tunnel,

72
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,960
there must be that hot dry rock you mentioned.

73
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,199
But since the Mengnagu people crossed it,

74
00:04:03,319 --> 00:04:04,879
there must be an insulating layer below.

75
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:06,520
If we find the insulated spots,

76
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,520
we can make it across.

77
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,080
Uncle Min.

78
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,680
Miss He, the book.

79
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:20,399
There's a detailed record here

80
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:22,199
about Xuanlei Heijing Shan.

81
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,920
Xuanlei Heijing Shan

82
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,959
is the only path to the altar.

83
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:28,800
It has three parts: Serpent God's Fire,

84
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,480
Serpent God's People, and Serpent God's Eye.

85
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,920
What... what does that mean?

86
00:04:32,279 --> 00:04:33,560
These all seem to symbolize

87
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,720
the forces of nature.

88
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,600
People had to use different methods

89
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,279
in the tunnels to show their worship

90
00:04:38,279 --> 00:04:39,560
for the Fire God who nurtured them,

91
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,759
and for the Serpent God.

92
00:04:41,439 --> 00:04:42,639
For the Serpent God's Fire,

93
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,480
you must dance with the priest to pass.

94
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,959
So this passage

95
00:04:50,199 --> 00:04:52,000
was used for rituals and worship.

96
00:04:52,399 --> 00:04:53,279
That's possible.

97
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,800
Many ancient civilizations had this tradition.

98
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,160
Take the Mayans, for example.

99
00:04:57,399 --> 00:04:59,000
They believed the sun

100
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,639
would eventually be destroyed.

101
00:05:00,639 --> 00:05:01,639
So they would use

102
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:03,120
self-sacrifice rituals

103
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,959
to preserve the sun's light.

104
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:09,000
Feeding the Sun God with hearts and blood.

105
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,839
And in Carthage in North Africa,

106
00:05:10,879 --> 00:05:13,800
they would even burn their own children

107
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,040
to worship the gods.

108
00:05:16,439 --> 00:05:17,879
How could they even do that?

109
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,639
But here's what I'm thinking.

110
00:05:21,079 --> 00:05:22,639
No matter what, right?

111
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:25,600
The priest can't die here, can he?

112
00:05:25,839 --> 00:05:26,319
Right.

113
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,360
He just dances and dances,

114
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,680
and then he makes it across.

115
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:33,120
The question is, what kind of dance?

116
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,439
And who here even knows how to dance?

117
00:05:35,639 --> 00:05:36,839
What dance?

118
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,360
We'll know once we try.

119
00:05:38,759 --> 00:05:39,399
Look,

120
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:42,639
China is vast, right?

121
00:05:42,639 --> 00:05:43,560
All kinds of dances.

122
00:05:43,879 --> 00:05:46,319
Let's start from the far north.

123
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,040
Northeastern Yangge, right?

124
00:05:49,279 --> 00:05:51,439
Watch. One, two, three.

125
00:05:52,319 --> 00:05:55,040
Any fire? Any fire? There's fire!

126
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:57,079
And he made it across.

127
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,879
What the heck?

128
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:01,639
I think it's a footwork pattern.

129
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,360
The key is in the feet.

130
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,560
Right? Look.

131
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:13,279
I think you guys should stop messing around.

132
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:15,720
It's clearly written right here.

133
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,199
You can't just keep dancing.

134
00:06:17,279 --> 00:06:19,839
Move, pause, then watch the next step.

135
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,800
I don't think that's right.

136
00:06:26,079 --> 00:06:28,439
Look, the movements are continuous.

137
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,040
You have to look around like this,

138
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,319
then turn this way and look again.

139
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:34,839
This is clearly martial arts.

140
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,839
See? See? See?

141
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,240
Like Wing Chun.

142
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,360
It's a dance, a dance.

143
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,800
It goes like this.

144
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,160
That's what it means!

145
00:06:50,439 --> 00:06:53,519
This is clearly Xinjiang dance, Sainaim!

146
00:06:53,519 --> 00:06:54,160
Martial arts, martial arts.

147
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:57,600
Yangge has this move too, look.

148
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,519
I told you, it's a Tibetan dance.

149
00:06:59,519 --> 00:07:01,319
You'd be burnt to a crisp before the end.

150
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:05,120
After all this talk,

151
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:07,720
who's going down to dance first?

152
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,519
Just keep throwing them.

153
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,120
You know what,

154
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,240
there's an easier way.

155
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,600
Find a big rocky hill and blow it up.

156
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:45,040
Then flip the rocks over and lay them down.

157
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,199
Problem solved.

158
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:50,199
You throw for a bit. My arm's killing me.

159
00:07:50,959 --> 00:07:51,879
No way.

160
00:08:07,959 --> 00:08:08,759
Look at that!

161
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,399
It's safe!

162
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:24,759
So this must be the insulation layer.

163
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:25,560
Yes.

164
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,360
It has to be, it has to be.

165
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,959
This is the insulation layer.

166
00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:30,240
We've got a shot.

167
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:33,879
Wait a minute.

168
00:08:43,759 --> 00:08:46,120
That one, that one, that one!

169
00:08:46,799 --> 00:08:47,559
That one didn't catch fire.

170
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,360
Look at that one.

171
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,200
If we'd known this earlier,

172
00:08:52,919 --> 00:08:54,240
we should've done this from the start.

173
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:56,639
Commander Chen, this trick actually works!

174
00:08:57,279 --> 00:08:58,480
It's a bit slow, sure,

175
00:08:58,799 --> 00:09:00,360
but if we test it with these rocks,

176
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,519
we can make it across!

177
00:09:02,879 --> 00:09:03,679
But...

178
00:09:04,399 --> 00:09:05,480
the path is so long,

179
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,399
we definitely don't have enough rocks.

180
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,159
We'd still have to blow up a mountain.

181
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:10,679
Here's the plan.

182
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,480
I'll go try first.

183
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,279
You guys wait here for me.

184
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,039
Okay, okay.

185
00:09:31,559 --> 00:09:32,519
Be careful!

186
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:48,960
That's way too risky.

187
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,480
I don't think it'll work.

188
00:09:50,799 --> 00:09:51,840
Then why don't you try it?

189
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,000
Exactly.

190
00:09:53,039 --> 00:09:54,879
Go risk getting burned,

191
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:55,960
and step down there to try it yourself.

192
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,000
Look,

193
00:10:05,799 --> 00:10:06,759
that spot works too.

194
00:10:14,679 --> 00:10:16,440
He's actually doing pretty well.

195
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,399
Got the hang of it.

196
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:25,480
Fatty.

197
00:10:25,679 --> 00:10:27,879
How does he know where to throw them?

198
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:29,799
My guess is,

199
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:30,879
once we go a bit further,

200
00:10:31,279 --> 00:10:33,559
this scorching stuff will be gone.

201
00:10:33,559 --> 00:10:34,360
Possibly.

202
00:10:34,399 --> 00:10:35,440
After that point,

203
00:10:35,759 --> 00:10:37,399
it's all insulation layers.

204
00:10:37,799 --> 00:10:38,759
I can do it too.

205
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,679
Let me give it a shot.

206
00:10:40,799 --> 00:10:42,159
I can do this too.

207
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,159
Why are you messing around?

208
00:10:51,799 --> 00:10:52,519
I'm just...

209
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,559
If you can do it, go ahead.

210
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:55,840
This, this...

211
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,519
That's why he's Commander Chen.

212
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,279
I got it.

213
00:11:05,519 --> 00:11:06,720
Follow my route.

214
00:11:06,919 --> 00:11:07,440
Let's go.

215
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,440
Everyone, watch the white stones on the ground.

216
00:11:09,679 --> 00:11:10,720
Don't step in the wrong spot.

217
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:17,399
Godfather, I'm going first.

218
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,879
Aren't you bringing stones?

219
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:22,879
We already have a route.

220
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,120
Shutong, did you find something?

221
00:11:36,039 --> 00:11:37,919
I've been studying our route.

222
00:11:38,679 --> 00:11:39,759
It seems

223
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:43,960
to match Taurus, Aries, and Gemini.

224
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,720
It lines up perfectly.

225
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,799
You mean

226
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,399
this mechanism and the stars above

227
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:50,879
are arranged the same way?

228
00:11:51,399 --> 00:11:52,320
You could say that.

229
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,240
Back in those times,

230
00:11:56,519 --> 00:11:58,840
they could chart constellations

231
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,120
with such accuracy.

232
00:12:01,799 --> 00:12:03,159
It shows how advanced

233
00:12:03,159 --> 00:12:04,600
that civilization really was.

234
00:12:05,399 --> 00:12:06,399
What's the use of being advanced?

235
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,679
Their nation still fell, didn't it?

236
00:12:10,279 --> 00:12:11,399
Old Lu, take it slow.

237
00:12:15,919 --> 00:12:17,000
That wasn't easy at all.

238
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,759
We finally all made it across.

239
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,639
Advisor He is right.

240
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:22,240
The heat-insulating stones down here,

241
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:24,200
they're all arranged according to a star map.

242
00:12:26,399 --> 00:12:27,879
So with each step,

243
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,279
you're stepping on those star points.

244
00:12:30,399 --> 00:12:31,480
Right, that's the idea.

245
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,600
The Mengnagu script, numerals, and statues,

246
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,840
all these signs indicate

247
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,679
they closely resemble the zodiac.

248
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,600
So I cross-referenced

249
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,240
the sequence of the zodiac signs.

250
00:12:41,879 --> 00:12:43,320
And I found that

251
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:46,360
at the start of this tunnel,

252
00:12:46,399 --> 00:12:48,000
the stones were arranged

253
00:12:48,039 --> 00:12:50,840
according to the first sign of the zodiac,

254
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,200
the star map of Aries.

255
00:12:55,279 --> 00:12:57,399
So the layout of the insulation zones here

256
00:12:57,399 --> 00:12:59,519
all follow the order of the zodiac.

257
00:12:59,759 --> 00:13:00,360
Right.

258
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,000
Fine, let's leave that behind us.

259
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:05,360
I think what matters most now

260
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:07,000
is finding where the altar is.

261
00:13:07,159 --> 00:13:08,919
Once this door opens, that's the altar.

262
00:13:09,279 --> 00:13:10,480
Let's focus on that first.

263
00:13:12,039 --> 00:13:12,679
Ram it!

264
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:17,080
We didn't even ram it, and it just opened.

265
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:43,919
Shutong.

266
00:13:44,799 --> 00:13:46,679
This must be what the Book of Mengnagu calls

267
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,000
the Serpent God's People, right?

268
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:49,840
Probably so.
